questions as well, I think

00:37:32.425 --> 00:37:33.962
Jeremy has a mic in the back.

00:37:33.962 --> 00:37:36.910
AUDIENCE: Yeah I want to
go back to your mentioning

00:37:36.910 --> 00:37:40.000
how much of an influence comic
books and reading science

00:37:40.000 --> 00:37:42.091
fiction was for Musk.

00:37:42.091 --> 00:37:43.840
One of the things I'm
really curious about

00:37:43.840 --> 00:37:47.100
is, looking at the industries
that he's taken on,

00:37:47.100 --> 00:37:52.980
it's very sort of like Modernist
perspective of transportation

00:37:52.980 --> 00:37:54.540
and energy.

00:37:54.540 --> 00:37:56.040
Even the way he's
thinking about AI,

00:37:56.040 --> 00:37:59.420
I'm curious if it's
reflecting this '50s,

00:37:59.420 --> 00:38:01.940
'60s view from science fiction.

00:38:01.940 --> 00:38:04.470
And meanwhile, when you think
about like Philip K. Dick,

00:38:04.470 --> 00:38:06.410
you think about
Cyberpunk, a lot more sort

00:38:06.410 --> 00:38:09.470
of engaging with identity,
how a human identity involved,

00:38:09.470 --> 00:38:12.460
how our composition evolves
through genetic engineering.

00:38:12.460 --> 00:38:15.400
Do you see him engaging
in some of these more

00:38:15.400 --> 00:38:17.762
recent preoccupations
