00:38:17.762 --> 00:38:19.220
ASHLEE VANCE: I
mean, first of all,

00:38:19.220 --> 00:38:21.000
I think your point
is exactly right.

00:38:21.000 --> 00:38:23.180
I mean, that's the
way I sort of came--

00:38:23.180 --> 00:38:26.630
your first point is the way
I came to view the companies.

00:38:26.630 --> 00:38:30.260
I mean, like the aerospace
stuff in particular

00:38:30.260 --> 00:38:32.010
is sort of depressing
outside of SpaceX.

00:38:32.010 --> 00:38:36.240
I would go to launches of
Arianespace and-- I mean,

00:38:36.240 --> 00:38:38.530
these companies
do amazing things.

00:38:38.530 --> 00:38:42.040
But the equipment looks
like it's from 1960s still.

00:38:42.040 --> 00:38:46.960
And you expect there to be
these kind of modern-- you just

00:38:46.960 --> 00:38:48.080
expect it to be advanced.

00:38:48.080 --> 00:38:49.080
And it just hasn't been.

00:38:49.080 --> 00:38:52.780
And SpaceX definitely has
put pressure on everybody

00:38:52.780 --> 00:38:56.120
to up their game on software,
all the electronics inside

00:38:56.120 --> 00:38:58.410
of the rockets, and
then more recently

00:38:58.410 --> 00:39:00.340
just with the way a
capsule should look.

00:39:00.340 --> 00:39:02.945
And Elon's going to come
out with new spacesuits

00:39:02.945 --> 00:39:04.650
soon that he says are crazy.

00:39:04.650 --> 00:39:06.890
And so, he's into
all that stuff.

00:39:06.890 --> 00:39:10.407
And then I think that
modernization of Tesla's

00:39:10.407 --> 00:39:12.240
pretty obvious, like
beyond the electric car

00:39:12.240 --> 00:39:14.540
stuff, the software in the car.

00:39:14.540 --> 00:39:17.830
It's funny because people ask
the second part of the question

00:39:17.830 --> 00:39:18.330
to me.

00:39:18.330 --> 00:39:20.410
Other times it's like, what?

00:39:20.410 --> 00:39:22.910
When's Elon going to cure
cancer or something like that.

00:39:22.910 --> 00:39:28.360
I don't he-- I just never
heard him really get

00:39:28.360 --> 00:39:34.730
into the biotech sort of-- I've
never heard him even address

00:39:34.730 --> 00:39:36.310
that stuff outside of industry.

00:39:36.310 --> 00:39:37.060
It's really funny.

00:39:37.060 --> 00:39:39.350
I mean, I think that's kind
of where he's locked in.

00:39:42.660 --> 00:39:45.890
Craig Venter and Elon
are pretty close.

00:39:45.890 --> 00:39:49.600
And they talk about these
biological 3D printers

00:39:49.600 --> 00:39:51.920
on Mars and where they
want to go with that.

00:39:51.920 --> 00:39:53.420
But that was the
only time I've ever

00:39:53.420 --> 00:39:58.500
heard him sort of even begin to
sort of veer in that direction.

00:39:58.500 --> 00:40:02.180
One of the central arguments I
try to make in the book is that

00:40:02.180 --> 00:40:04.466
Elon's-- I give you
guys credit, too,

00:40:04.466 --> 00:40:07.750
but Elon is one of our best
examples-- I think the best--

00:40:07.750 --> 00:40:09.930
of combining atoms and bits.

00:40:09.930 --> 00:40:13.090
And this is obviously
going to be this huge trend

00:40:13.090 --> 00:40:18.590
that we see in the next couple
decades of-- essentially

00:40:18.590 --> 00:40:24.200
what he's done is take Silicon
Valley, just the way you run

00:40:24.200 --> 00:40:27.850
your business, more like the
way companies are run here,

00:40:27.850 --> 00:40:30.110
and then the software
ethos and sort of push that

00:40:30.110 --> 00:40:32.720
into these industries
that were not prepared yet

00:40:32.720 --> 00:40:34.900
to move at that speed
or think that way.

00:40:34.900 --> 00:40:40.194
There's examples
in the book where

00:40:40.194 --> 00:40:42.110
if you want to put
a radio on a rocket,

00:40:42.110 --> 00:40:45.770
NASA would make you put
this $100,000 space grade

00:40:45.770 --> 00:40:46.970
radio on the rocket.

00:40:46.970 --> 00:40:48.960
And I'm sure that
was because they

00:40:48.960 --> 00:40:51.210
used to worry about the
radiation and all these things

00:40:51.210 --> 00:40:52.490
messing with the electronics.

00:40:52.490 --> 00:40:56.070
And then SpaceX was building
their own for $5,000.

00:40:56.070 --> 00:40:58.320
And they would have to fly
it up like a bunch of times

00:40:58.320 --> 00:40:59.944
and prove to them
that it still worked.

00:40:59.944 --> 00:41:03.350
Or that they could put four
of the $5,000 radios on.

00:41:03.350 --> 00:41:08.870
And so, to me, Elon
invents a lot of stuff,

00:41:08.870 --> 00:41:11.780
but he's this great integrator
of technologies and pushing

00:41:11.780 --> 00:41:14.382
these industries forward.

00:41:14.382 --> 00:41:15.840
