00:41:16.590 --> 00:41:17.872
ASHLEE VANCE: Oh, thank you.

00:41:17.872 --> 00:41:19.830
AUDIENCE: Now that the
book has been published,

00:41:19.830 --> 00:41:22.878
what is Elon's response?

00:41:22.878 --> 00:41:24.760
Did he get a chance
to read it before?

00:41:24.760 --> 00:41:28.114
And have you guys-- are you
guys still on communication?

00:41:28.114 --> 00:41:29.655
ASHLEE VANCE: Yeah,
it's complicated.

00:41:34.420 --> 00:41:37.540
Even though he didn't
get to make any changes,

00:41:37.540 --> 00:41:39.485
I didn't want him to
have to buy it on Amazon

00:41:39.485 --> 00:41:43.030
and speed read through it
before anything happens.

00:41:43.030 --> 00:41:46.420
So I think it was about three
weeks before the book came out.

00:41:46.420 --> 00:41:48.640
The presses had started
and all that stuff.

00:41:48.640 --> 00:41:50.590
So I sent him a copy.

00:41:50.590 --> 00:41:53.459
And then he did this
very Elon thing.

00:41:53.459 --> 00:41:55.250
I woke up one morning,
and the first email,

00:41:55.250 --> 00:41:58.480
the timestamp was like 3:30 AM.

00:41:58.480 --> 00:42:01.340
And he had been going
through the book paragraph

00:42:01.340 --> 00:42:02.015
by paragraph.

00:42:02.015 --> 00:42:03.390
And it was sort
of like-- I mean,

00:42:03.390 --> 00:42:04.870
it was all-- it
was a mix of stuff.

00:42:04.870 --> 00:42:09.350
Kind of silly things like, I
don't really eat like that.

00:42:09.350 --> 00:42:11.600
And then other things, like,
yeah, you got this right.

00:42:11.600 --> 00:42:12.920
And it was all over the place.

00:42:12.920 --> 00:42:14.220
It was actually kind of cool.

00:42:17.220 --> 00:42:21.770
He's like there's three
factually wrong things.

00:42:21.770 --> 00:42:23.950
And two of them were
opinions of him,

00:42:23.950 --> 00:42:25.920
which I was trying to
explain were not facts.

00:42:25.920 --> 00:42:31.670
And then the third one, he
said that Kimbal, his brother,

00:42:31.670 --> 00:42:33.622
had bought this car.

00:42:33.622 --> 00:42:35.080
They had a
cross-country road trip.

00:42:35.080 --> 00:42:36.780
And he's like, I bought
the car, not Kimbal.

00:42:36.780 --> 00:42:38.610
I was like, OK, I'm sure we
can get to the bottom of that

00:42:38.610 --> 00:42:40.180
before the paperback comes out.

00:42:40.180 --> 00:42:45.760
And then there were a
couple nastier emails.

00:42:45.760 --> 00:42:46.750
And then a day went by.

00:42:46.750 --> 00:42:48.625
And then he came back,
and he said, you know,

00:42:48.625 --> 00:42:49.720
this is really well done.

00:42:49.720 --> 00:42:54.980
And he gave me an
accuracy rating of 95%.

00:42:54.980 --> 00:43:02.230
Which like in Elon terms, I
take that as 100% for mortals.

00:43:02.230 --> 00:43:05.290
And then basically
those three weeks passed

00:43:05.290 --> 00:43:07.820
and the book came out,
and then some of the press

00:43:07.820 --> 00:43:10.550
started grabbing-- like
"The Washington Post" did

00:43:10.550 --> 00:43:13.960
this list of the juiciest quotes
or whatever from the book.

00:43:13.960 --> 00:43:16.610
And there were a couple
there, like one he

00:43:16.610 --> 00:43:19.730
said he was a samurai
and he would not fail.

00:43:19.730 --> 00:43:24.570
And then the other one was about
during Tesla's rougher times,

00:43:24.570 --> 00:43:27.100
him giving this
employee a hard time

00:43:27.100 --> 00:43:29.370
for going to see the
birth of his child

00:43:29.370 --> 00:43:32.410
when he was supposed
to be at a big meeting.

00:43:32.410 --> 00:43:35.780
And that was weird,
when people reacted

00:43:35.780 --> 00:43:39.030
to that in a
negative way, then he

00:43:39.030 --> 00:43:40.730
reacted in a pretty
negative way.

00:43:40.730 --> 00:43:43.960
It was weird because
he'd never even commented

00:43:43.960 --> 00:43:47.540
on either of those things
when he read the book.

00:43:47.540 --> 00:43:49.540
And so then he got
[INAUDIBLE] for a little bit.

00:43:49.540 --> 00:43:52.690
And then things have been
pretty normal since then.

00:43:52.690 --> 00:43:55.260
I sort of covered
some Tesla stuff.

00:43:55.260 --> 00:43:56.790
He's back together
with Tallulha.

00:43:56.790 --> 00:43:59.090
And she's been quite nice to me.

00:43:59.090 --> 00:44:01.110
So I don't know.

00:44:01.110 --> 00:44:05.320
Things are still a little
tense, but not horrible.

00:44:05.320 --> 00:44:08.060
AUDIENCE: To what
extent do you think

00:44:08.060 --> 00:44:11.360
a lot of what Musk is doing
is a reaction to a failure

00:44:11.360 --> 00:44:14.250
of our institutions?

